cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing tasks and proposes a method to improve the understanding of rare words in deep language models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep neural network architectures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method to adapt Attentive Mimicking to deep language models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of subword-based tokenization, which could relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions a novel dataset that tests the ability of language models to capture semantic properties of words, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
